{"title":"Scythe","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Scythe","type":"markdown","data":"| ) [![Scythe.png](/images/c/cd/Scythe.png)](/wiki/File:Scythe.png) |                                                        |\n| ----------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------ |\n| Name                                                              | scythe                                                 |\n| Appearance                                                        | scythe                                                 |\n| Damage vs. small                                                  | 1d8+1d4                                                |\n| Damage vs. large                                                  | 1d10+1d4                                               |\n| To-hit bonus                                                      | +0                                                     |\n| Weapon skill                                                      | [polearms](/wiki/Polearms \"Polearms\")                  |\n| Size                                                              | [one-handed](/wiki/One-handed \"One-handed\")            |\n| Base price                                                        | 5 [zm](/wiki/Zorkmid \"Zorkmid\") (+10/positive enchant) |\n| Weight                                                            | [60](/wiki/Weight \"Weight\")                            |\n| Material                                                          | [iron](/wiki/Iron \"Iron\")                              |\n\nA **scythe** is a type of two-handed [weapon](/wiki/Weapon \"Weapon\") that appears in *[dNetHack](/wiki/DNetHack \"DNetHack\")*, *[SpliceHack](/wiki/SpliceHack \"SpliceHack\")* and *[Hack'EM](/wiki/Hack%27EM \"Hack'EM\")*.\n\n[ ]\n\n## Contents\n\n- [1 Generation](#Generation)\n\n- [2 History](#History)\n\n- [3 Variants](#Variants)\n\n  - [3.1 SLASHTHEM](#SLASHTHEM)\n  - [3.2 dNetHack](#dNetHack)\n\n## Generation\n\nScythes do not generate randomly.\n\nIn SpliceHack and Hack'EM, [redcaps](/wiki/Redcap \"Redcap\") and [Death](/wiki/Death \"Death\") always get a scythe. In these variants, [The End](/wiki/The_End \"The End\") is also the only [artifact](/wiki/Artifact_weapon \"Artifact weapon\") scythe.\n\nIn Hack'EM, [peasants](/wiki/Peasant \"Peasant\") have a 1⁄5 chance of generating with a scythe.\n\n## History\n\nThe scythe first appears in [dNetHack](/wiki/DNetHack \"DNetHack\"). SpliceHack created a [grain scythe](/wiki/Grain_scythe \"Grain scythe\") that appears to be influenced by the dNetHack scythe, but it was later renamed to just [scythe]().\n\nThe [grain scythe](/wiki/Grain_scythe \"Grain scythe\") was ported from SpliceHack to [SLASHTHEM](/wiki/SLASHTHEM \"SLASHTHEM\").\n\n[Hack'EM](/wiki/Hack%27EM \"Hack'EM\") later ported the latter [scythe]() from SpliceHack.\n\n## Variants\n\n### SLASHTHEM\n\nGrain scythes get +6 to-hit and +20 damage vs [straw golems](/wiki/Straw_golem \"Straw golem\").\n\nIn SLASHTHEM, the grain scythe only does d8 vs small monsters.\n\n### dNetHack\n\n| ) [![Scythe.png](/images/c/cd/Scythe.png)](/wiki/File:Scythe.png) |                                                                                             |\n| ----------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Name                                                              | scythe                                                                                      |\n| Appearance                                                        | scythe                                                                                      |\n| Damage vs. small                                                  | 2d4                                                                                         |\n| Damage vs. large                                                  | 2d4                                                                                         |\n| To-hit bonus                                                      | -2                                                                                          |\n| Weapon skill                                                      | [harvest](/index.php?title=Harvest\\&action=edit\\&redlink=1 \"Harvest (page does not exist)\") |\n| Size                                                              | [one-handed](/wiki/One-handed \"One-handed\")                                                 |\n| Base price                                                        | 6 [zm](/wiki/Zorkmid \"Zorkmid\") (+10/positive enchant)                                      |\n| Weight                                                            | [75](/wiki/Weight \"Weight\")                                                                 |\n| Material                                                          | [iron](/wiki/Iron \"Iron\")                                                                   |\n\nVs plants, scythes get +6 to hit and double damage.\n\n[![This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.6. Click here for more information.](/images/5/57/Nh366-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.6. Click here for more information.\")\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Scythe - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Scythe\",\"wgTitle\":\"Scythe\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":162909,\"wgRevisionId\"