2.163      2 Template:Cyan\",\" 17.35%    2.145      1 Template:Top_icon\",\" 10.99%    1.359      1 Template:Frac\"]},\"cachereport\":{\"timestamp\":\"20240926190316\",\"ttl\":604800,\"transientcontent\":false}}});mw.config.set({\"wgBackendResponseTime\":95});});</script>\n\t</body>\n</html>\n","rawPage":"{{weapon\n |color=metal color\n |tile=[[image:scythe.png]]\n |name=scythe\n |smalldmg=1d8+1d4\n |largedmg=1d10+1d4\n |skill=polearms\n |cost=5\n |weight=60\n |material=iron\n}}\n\nA '''scythe''' is a type of two-handed [[weapon]] that appears in ''[[dNetHack]]'', ''[[SpliceHack]]'' and  ''[[Hack'EM]]''. \n\n==Generation==\n\nScythes do not generate randomly.\n\nIn SpliceHack and Hack'EM, [[redcap]]s and [[Death]] always get a scythe. In these variants, [[The End]] is also the only [[artifact weapon|artifact]] scythe.\n\nIn Hack'EM, [[peasant]]s have a {{frac|5}} chance of generating with a scythe.\n\n==History==\n\nThe scythe first appears in [[dNetHack]]. SpliceHack created a [[grain scythe]] that appears to be influenced by the dNetHack scythe, but it was later renamed to just [[scythe]]. \n\nThe [[grain scythe]] was ported from SpliceHack to [[SLASHTHEM]].\n\n[[Hack'EM]] later ported the latter [[scythe]] from SpliceHack.\n\n==Variants==\n=== SLASHTHEM ===\n\nGrain scythes get +6 to-hit and +20 damage vs [[straw golem]]s.\n\nIn SLASHTHEM, the grain scythe only does d8 vs small monsters.\n\n=== dNetHack ===\n{{weapon\n |color=metal color\n |tile=[[image:scythe.png]]\n |name=scythe\n |smalldmg=2d4\n |largedmg=2d4\n |tohit=<nowiki>-2</nowiki>\n |skill=harvest\n |cost=6\n |weight=75\n |material=iron\n}}\n\nVs plants, scythes get +6 to hit and double damage.\n\n{{nethack-366}}\n[[Category:SpliceHack]]\n[[Category:Hack'EM]]\n[[Category:Weapons]]"}